    On Thursday, November 2, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region [CEDER] accompanied by other members of CEDER executed a residential search warrant upon 103 Austin Circle, Berlin, Maryland. Matthew Powell [hereinafter referred to as "Matthew"] opened the front door after I made several knocks and announces. The residence was cleared by members of CEDER and the only other person present at the residence was Powell's daughter identified as Kyleigh Powell [hereinafter referred to as "Kyleigh"]. One hundred and twenty-five (125) digital images were taken during the execution of the search warrant, and later uploaded to VeriPic in accordance with MSP policy.     At approximately 0611 hours [6:11 a.m.] I attempted to conduct an audibly and visually recorded interview with Matthew, however he declined to speak with me. I read Matthew the search warrant which was captured audibly and visually. At approximately 0619 hours [6:19 a.m.] I spoke with Kyleigh and read her a Maryland State Police form 78 (consent to search and seize) and explained to her that if she provides written consent, for me to preview her cell phone and verify her cellular phone contained no CSAM. Kyliegh provided written consent for me to search and preview her iPhone 11, and I did not find any CSAM on the phone. Kyleigh was immediately given her iPhone 11 back, and she left the residence. 

    Matthew was provided copies of the search warrant, search warrant return, and inventory, and then myself and CEDER investigators exited the residence and responded to the Maryland State Police Berlin Barrack with the seized evidence which was processed and stored in accordance with MSP policy.

Narrative: 
    On Monday, November 6, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region conducted and audibly and visually recorded interview with Laura Powell [hereinafter referred to as "Laura"] concerning the investigation. The interview was conducted in the Maryland State Police Salisbury Barrack interview room. Below is a synopsis of the interview and not a transcript therefore some paraphrasing may be used;
  • Laura was shown the Cyber-Tip and the details listed on it concerning suspect information.
  • Laura was shown the listed suspect email address, beachbum92278@gmail.com, and advised the numbers 92278 are Matthew Powell's [hereinafter referred to as "Matthew"] birth date.
  • Laura was shown the Google subscriber information which listed a backup email account of: map719@gmail.com which Laura positively identified as Matthew's email account. 
  • Laura also identified the email address listed by Comcast, which was MP719@comcast.net, and added that 719 is their daughter's birth date. 
  • Laura and Matthew have been divorced since 2021, and Matthew lives with only his daughter at 103 Austin Circle, Berlin, Maryland.
  • Laura added that Matthew has a girlfriend that may stay with him. 
  • Laura was aware of Matthew watching pornography but not child pornography. 
Case OPEN
